tischen Denkens rekonstruiert, die im zweiten Teil des Buches mit Blick auf genuin kritische Deutungsmöglichkeiten realpolitischer Geschehnisse veranschaulicht werden.  aThe increasing Americanization of political science and the discipline of international relations has rendered the profile of an independent scholarly perspective vis-à-vis (international) politics almost unrecognizable. This book reconstructs important basic principles of critical thinking, which are illustrated with a view to genuinely critical interpretations of real political events.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aHistorischer Materialismus. 4aKritische Theorie. 4aPostkritik. 4aPoststrukturalismus. 4aTheorien der Internationalen Beziehungen. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aFeminism.  aInternational relations.  aPostmodernism.  aTheory of imperialism.  aTheory.  aWorld systems theory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023z9783111318677oZDB-23-PLW0 cEPUBz97831104729120 cprintz978348676186340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311047125040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110471250423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110471250/original  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-PLWb2023